HEADWORD: Simonian
<hw>Si*mo"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[See
<er>Simony</er>.]</ety> <def>One of the followers of Simon Magus; also,
an adherent of certain heretical sects in the early Christian
church.</def>⟦br⟧
